<ul>
<li>1 tbsp butter</li>
<li>1/2 cup water</li>
<li>1 tbsp honey&nbsp;</li>
<li>1 tbsp brown sugar</li>
<li>Shrimp&nbsp;</li>
<li>2 eggs</li>
<li>1/2 cup corn starch</li>
<li>3 tbsp mayo&nbsp;</li>
<li>1 tbsp honey</li>
<li>1 tsp lemon juice</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Instructions</span></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Caramelize butter with water, honey, and sugar over medium heat (wait for it to bubble)</li>
<li>Add walnuts and cook for 5 minutes</li>
<li>Remove and separate on pan</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>Season shrimp with salt and pepper</li>
<li>Scramble eggs and coat shrimp</li>
<li>Coat shrimp with corn starch</li>
<li>Pan fry shrimp and return walnuts to pan</li>
<li>Coat with sauce</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
