('e7b53eb2-aa95-4c3e-92d5-8e6fd2d7c4d8', '64ed428e-10b7-428e-b584-e3b6378cb171', 'Double pie crust', 'dessert', '', '', '<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>2&frac12;&nbsp; (325 grams) cups all-purpose flour, plus more to dust</li>
<li>1 tsp salt</li>
<li>&frac12; tbsp sugar</li>
<li>1 cup of very cold unsalted butter (2 sticks), cut into &frac12; inch&nbsp;</li>
<li>4 to 8 tbsp ice water&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Instructions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Pulse dry ingredients to combine</li>
<li>Add butter and pulse until coarse crumbs form with some lima bean size pieces; should remain dry and powdery</li>
<li>Slowly add ice water, 1 tbsp at a time, and pulse until dough comes together; should be moist, but not wet
<ul>
<li>If you pinch some of the dough and it holds together, it&rsquo;s ready.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Gather dough together into a ball (do not knead); divide in half and flatten to disks</li>
<li>Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour</li>
<li>Rolling out:
<ul>
<li>Remove dough from refrigerator and let sit for 5 minutes</li>
<li>Flour surface, dough, and rolling pin</li>
<li>Roll to fit pie dish with 1 inch edge over the circumference&nbsp;</li>
<li>Transfer to pie dish and trim if necessary</li>
<li>Tuck the edge inwards, but don&rsquo;t crimp until the top is on</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>', false),
