('295050b4-a507-4a56-a264-1b39136009b9', '64ed428e-10b7-428e-b584-e3b6378cb171', 'Claire Saffitz''s Chocolate Chip Cookies', 'dessert', 'Best cookies ever', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kPauR6tP_cg&t=105s', '<p>Ingredients:</p>
<pre>2 sticks unsalted butter (8 oz / 227g), cut into tablespoons
2 tablespoons heavy cream, half-and-half, or whole milk (1 oz / 28g)
2 cups all-purpose flour (9.2 oz / 260g)
2 teaspoons Diamond Crystal kosher salt (0.22 oz / 6g)
1 teaspoon baking soda (0.21 oz / 6g)
3/4 cup packed dark brown sugar (5.3 oz / 150g)
3/4 cup granulated sugar (5.3 oz / 150g)
2 large eggs (3.5 oz / 100g), cold from the refrigerator 
1 tablespoon vanilla extract
5 ounces (142g) bittersweet chocolate disks, half coarsely chopped
5 ounces (142g) milk chocolate disks, half coarsely chopped</pre>
<p>Instructions:</p>
<ul>
<li>brown butter over low heat; pour into mixing bowl</li>
<li>add 2 tbsp of heavy cream or milk and let it cool down</li>
<li>add equal amounts of white and brown sugar; mix</li>
<li>add eggs one at a time and mix</li>
<li>add vanilla and mix</li>
<li>in a separate bowl:&nbsp; mix flour, baking soda, salt (if morton use only 1 tsp!)&nbsp;</li>
<li>add dry ingredients into mixing bowl and mix</li>
<li>add chocolate and stir in&nbsp;</li>
<li>portion out dough and chill for at least a couple hours in the fridge</li>
<li>pre-heat oven to 350 degrees</li>
<li>bake for 10 minutes then switch racks to ensure even cooking</li>
<li>bake for 18-22 minutes total until golden brown edge</li>
</ul>', false),
