('9b707f7a-ce9b-4ea1-a1ee-a55ed9050ef0', 'adb964f4-fdb5-41cb-ab5d-25bb9099e6ac', 'Vegan queso', 'side', '', '', '<div>- 3/4 cup oat milk</div>
<div>- 1 cup nuts (I''ve been doing half almonds, half cashews but I think it would be fine to use all cashews). Toast them in a skillet for a few minutes first</div>
<div>- 1 medium red bell pepper, core removed</div>
<div>- 1 chipotle pepper + a bit of the sauce (I recommend buying a <a href="https://mestizomarket.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/product_c_h_chipotles_en_adobo_lc.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://mestizomarket.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/product_c_h_chipotles_en_adobo_lc.png&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1638193999693000&amp;usg=AOvVaw0mhe-PHaCfFHScGe2P9eHn">can of chipotles in adobo sauce</a> from the Mexican aisle. You can save what you don''t use in a tupperware)</div>
<div>- 1/4 cup nutritional yeast</div>
<div>- Salt to taste (up to a teaspoon)</div>
<div>- 1/2 teaspoon of turmeric (optional)</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Blend all ingredients 5/6 minutes, until the mixture is physically hot. Lasts about a week in the fridge. Tasty cold or hot!</div>', false),
